article.headline: Samford 55, Murray State 44
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Center Travis Peterson scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Samford in a 55-44 win Thursday night against Murray State. The Bulldogs remained undefeated in Ohio Valley Conference play, improving to 3-0 and 5-4 overall. Murray State falls to 3-2 in the OVC and 5-8 overall. Samford's smothering defense held Murray State to 32 percent shooting in the second half, while the Bulldogs shot 48 percent. OVC-leading scorer Randall Gulina added 13 points and five boards for the Bulldogs. Murray State led for most of the first half, but fell behind when Peterson hit a 3-pointer with seven seconds left to give the Bulldogs a 25-22 lead at the break. Samford started the second half on an 18-9 run and held the Racers scoreless for six minutes following a Tyler Holloway free throw at 13:11. Murray State looked as if it might make a run when the Racers scored two consecutive baskets to cut the lead to eight with less than six minutes left, but a 3-pointer by Samford guard Jerry Smith followed by a Peterson jumper gave Samford the victory. Junior guard Bruce Carter led Murray State with 19 points and five rebounds. Ray George contributed 10 points and added two assists in just his second game as a Racer.
